OL,3,CTeachers to take industrial action
OL,4,Cafter rejecting pay offer
OL,6,F"INTO remains committed to finding an
OL,7,Fuplift that is acceptable to our
OL,8,Fmembers, in the meantime."
OL,10,FNITC vice chair Justin McCamphill, who
OL,11,Fis also an NASUWT national official,
OL,12,Fsaid: "Our members have made clear
OL,13,Fthat the offer as presented to them
OL,14,Flast week was not acceptable.
OL,16,F"Management side need to draft a pay
OL,17,Foffer which will meet the legitimate
OL,18,Fexpectations of teachers, action short
OL,19,Fof strike action will commence on
OL,20,FMonday."
