OL,3,CTeachers to take industrial action
OL,4,Cafter rejecting pay offer
OL,6,FChair of the management side Eve
OL,7,FBremner said the offer was "at the
OL,8,Fvery limits of affordability", adding
OL,9,Fthat the planned industrial action
OL,10,Fwill have "serious implications for
OL,11,Fchildren and young people's education".
OL,13,FShe said the management side has asked
OL,14,Fthe NITC to suspend the planned
OL,15,Findustrial action and to bring forward
OL,16,Fproposals to resolve this dispute.
OL,18,F"We are committed to achieving the
OL,19,Fbest possible outcomes for pupils and
OL,20,Fteaching staff," Ms Bremner said.
